By construction, the columns of P are standardized, mutually uncorrelated time series. Each column is associated with a pattern of loadings (from the corresponding column of matrix E) on the original m variables and with the amount of variance (given by the corresponding diagonal element in Λ) that it explains within the total variance of the m original variables. The latter is easy to see from observing that the variance-covariance matrix of the original variables:8\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
